Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon discovering that her mom \Nhad never forgotten her, Luise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.12,0:00:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,was on the verge of shouting "Mom, Luise is right here!" \Nfrom the bottom of her lungs.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.79,0:00:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Luise wouldn't break her promise to Lotte. \N Not of her own accord, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:23.34,Sign,,0,0,105,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 10 \N {\fs35} Birth of a Genius Pianist {天才ピアニスト誕生} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.12,0:00:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, we've been invited \Nto give an opera performance in Berlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I will be away for about a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.95,0:00:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need help with something while I'm away, \Nfeel free to consult with Doctor Strobl. Deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.19,0:00:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.20,0:00:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave with an easy heart, Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.80,0:00:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm also going to come by every now and then, \Nto make sure the girl is doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.85,0:01:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... In that case, please let me bring you \Nsome dazzling souvenir as a "Thank you."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.01,0:01:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can but to look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.78,0:01:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you give me a chock-full list of souvenirs \Nyou want me to bring back this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.82,0:01:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A list? {not sure it's this, sounds like a weird place to put in wasei eigo, maybe "with a squirrel"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.09,0:01:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than souvenirs, \NI'd like you back soon and in good health.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.39,0:01:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Luise! Those words stem \Nfrom the genuine goodwill.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.72,0:01:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To return to you possibly sooner \Nand in good health is my wish, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.97,0:01:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we finish performing, \NI'll take a plane to fly back to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.50,0:01:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria Therese. {guess, not in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.01,0:01:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say she has the world's number one soprano voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.34,0:01:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,World's number one in putting on airs, too. \NI hope they hold contests in that. {not sure what he means: Whether it will work or not}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.05,0:01:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As luck would have it, I have reasons to think \Nyou will conduct her performance, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.22,0:01:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we'll see what comes out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.54,0:02:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'll be back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.11,0:02:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do, dad! \N In good health!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.38,0:02:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.82,0:02:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's darn good!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.57,0:02:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.79,0:03:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.09,0:03:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Much obliged.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much. Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.56,0:03:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.16,0:03:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold there, little one. \NYou don't have to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.06,0:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.39,0:03:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not accepting money from those younger than me \Nis one of my policies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.41,0:03:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But I also had a lot of fun, \Non the same level as all the grown-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.27,0:03:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So I {\i1}should{\i0} pay up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.52,0:03:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, our household budget \Neasily allows for that. {act. "living expenses are a whole other thing" but I've no clue what she means and why the guy is so surprised at it}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.28,0:03:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Household budget?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.57,0:03:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I should still have enough here to buy meat, \Nvegetables and bread from the market on my way home. {lit: on my way home, I'll go to market to buy ...  - no clue what's the relation to prev. lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, wouldn't it be better to use this money \Nto return home with a bigger piece of meat instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.49,0:03:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Little Housekeeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.77,0:03:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But how?! How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.70,0:03:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we... meet before in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.91,0:03:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.61,0:03:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I considered visiting it at least once. \NThey say, street performers there always eat their fill. {prosperous; flourishing; thriving; successful}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.61,0:03:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? But why, then, \Nwould you call me a little housekeeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you said you're managing \Nyour household budget and doing groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:03:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's something housekeepers do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.65,0:03:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.98,0:04:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you mean to say \Nyou're working as an actual housekeeper in your age?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.42,0:04:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.39,0:04:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.70,0:04:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They call me Hans of the Winds. \NNice to meet you. {can't be 100% sure but I hope it's japanese kaze no}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.27,0:04:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans of the Winds?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.15,0:04:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it sickens me to reside in just one place, \NI'm always on the road, just like the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.53,0:04:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Born as Hans Stefan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.29,0:04:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.71,0:04:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.38,0:04:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Any chance you're a daughter of Ludwig Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.65,0:04:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's straight-up silly!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.91,0:04:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.89,0:04:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, imagine - a daughter of a famous conductor \Nand composer hanging out with me just like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.29,0:04:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it..?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.09,0:04:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, as a fellow musician, \NI hold Herr Palfy in highest esteem!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.47,0:04:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you happen to actually be his daughter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.97,0:04:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,would you, by any chance, \Nlet me see his atelier just for a second?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.08,0:04:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.34,0:04:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To my dad, his atelier is a sacred ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.95,0:05:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for a second or two, to breathe the same air, \Nsame scent as the great master would be enough for me! {/to taste the same air, fragrance as the first class person, even if just once, I want}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.92,0:05:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you're asking so earnestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.70,0:05:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I could let you take a peek. {/only if you just look}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.92,0:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.67,0:05:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr concierge, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.21,0:05:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Fraulein Luise. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is my friend, \Nhis name is Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.15,0:05:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise. Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.84,0:06:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this Herr Palfy's atelier?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.02,0:06:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is where Herr Palfy \Nsits while composing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a first-class piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.26,0:06:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet, it sounds wonderful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.50,0:06:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans, you play piano?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.65,0:06:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Just a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to try?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.68,0:06:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, of course... Ah... \NNo, I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be sufficiently content \Njust being let into Herr Palfy's atelier.{ whom I worship/adore}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.89,0:06:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind, try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.26,0:06:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta be kidding! \NTo have me, some street performer, play {\i1}this{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.63,0:06:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.79,0:06:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Most seriously serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.17,0:06:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But for me, to play this piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I get to play a real piano... {I wanted to try playing a real piano - this is lit, but this doesn't make sense, he clearly played piano before}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.92,0:07:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're good, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.67,0:07:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bungled the last part. \NIt's been a while since I last played it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,For a first performance in a while, \Nthis sounded amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.54,0:08:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'd rather listen to you doing it, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.95,0:08:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.85,0:08:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You can play, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.33,0:08:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Just... not now. {/I can't}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.03,0:08:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not now? Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.18,0:08:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to, but at the moment, I'm my other self -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise who can't play the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.64,0:08:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a pity. {lit is " to live in luxury; to indulge oneself" and idk what he means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Pity?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.54,0:08:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,When you got a piano that exceptional,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.55,0:08:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and you got the teaching from your dad who is a composer, \Nrefusing to play it for someone is a real waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.68,0:08:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If I were you, I'd be playing it for days on end, \Nto be perfectly honest! {/every day for many hours}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.89,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could play it, too. However...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.39,0:08:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.66,0:08:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was my pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.50,0:08:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then. \NI need to make some more coin today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.69,0:08:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.58,0:08:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad would be away for about a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.77,0:08:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, feel free to come play piano anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.73,0:08:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For real? \NMan, that's a godsend!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.65,0:09:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,By then, I hope Luise lets me hear her play, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.10,0:09:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I'm convinced! \NMom's cooking is better every time!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.19,0:09:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just letting you know, \Nflattery won't help increasing your allowance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Saw it right through! {hope its bareta ka}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.78,0:09:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, mom, you should let me \Ndo the cooking sometimes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you get so hung up on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to let go of your sense of duty sometimes, \Nspending time in leisure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I would only resort to asking you for help \Nwhen I'm too busy myself, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.98,0:09:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! The phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll answer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.09,0:09:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be a call from Lotte again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.16,0:09:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.31,0:09:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte Körner listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.17,0:09:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A thorn in your mom's side is calling. {/fighting friend}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.96,0:09:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief Bernau! \NI'm giving you mom right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.97,0:09:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.63,0:09:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? This is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.47,0:09:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Recent development of things suggests \Nmaking next month's issue an opera-focused special. {/I want to put together a special article about opera}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.64,0:10:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In three days, I want you \Nto go to Berlin for the field work. {/to take interviews}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Need you to interview \NMaria Therese and Ludwig Palfy. {who would be there in combination}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.69,0:10:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you have to take care of Lotte, \Nbut we really have nobody else that suited for the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.66,0:10:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm having to bother you for this. {warui ga itte kurenai ka?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.69,0:10:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. \NI don't see why I shouldn't be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.73,0:10:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whew, you're a saver.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll book two tickets, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.76,0:10:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming as a moral support, too. See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.47,0:10:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.30,0:10:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So sorry, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.12,0:10:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, I'll be away for some time \Ndue to a work assignment. {/to take interviews}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.41,0:10:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave with an easy heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.91,0:10:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you do your best \Nduring that assignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with Hans? 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.17,0:10:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He never came today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.71,0:11:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, and pardon the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.05,0:11:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... But who might the Frau be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What... What's all of this? Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.89,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my goodness, \Nwhat's this sumptuous feast? {extravagant; lavish; opulent; luxurious; magnificent; splendid; fancy; gorgeous}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.50,0:11:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, little Luise. As you can see, \NI'm not taking a promise I made to your father lightly. {cam eot fullfill }
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.17,0:11:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein, you know the Frau?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.74,0:11:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a friend of dad's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.01,0:11:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Master's friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.81,0:11:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This dinner has been prepared for Fraulein Luise \Nby my best cook on my request.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.57,0:11:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,But a dinner for Fraulein \Nis something I can handle myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.38,0:11:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, aren't you happy \Nto be relieved of your duties tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.21,0:11:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We have included your share, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.62,0:11:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Included my share? My, my! \NThat is the most welcomed favor, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.82,0:11:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, Luise. I will come again \Nwith another one of those in a matter of few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.81,0:12:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.87,0:12:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care! We would be happy \Nto see you on our doorstep again!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.07,0:12:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Fraulein, let's get to eating right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi, you can have it all to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.99,0:12:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you really let me \Neat all of that myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.93,0:12:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Just heavenly! \NOf course, Master's friend is a noble person! {/she's a really good ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.78,0:12:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't believe Hans is not coming today either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.29,0:12:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Peperl!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.99,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you find Hans with your nose?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.44,0:13:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Hans, why didn't you \Ncome over to play the piano again?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.41,0:13:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, after I played it once, \NI've come to realize one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.03,0:13:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I won't be able \Nto part with this fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.93,0:14:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I was small, I was toiling as a bootblack, \Nsaving some coin day by day, until finally, I could buy this. {act. "was working with all my might at shoe store; shoe shop; shoemaker" but that's not as expressive}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.02,0:14:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since then, he is a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.06,0:14:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we do everything together, even sleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.86,0:14:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Noble! Becoming friends with your instrument.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's also why I won't be able to dump this friend \Nto replace him with a piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, one day, us two \Nwill be playing on the stages of the world, too! {/will see first-class music}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.71,0:14:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,On the very same ones as your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.44,0:14:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, for Hans, it's doable! Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.41,0:14:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, the key to music \Nis being passionate about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.62,0:14:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm passionate enough about it, \Nnobody can stop me. {/the power that doesn't lose to anyone - passion}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.31,0:14:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mozart, Beethoven, Strauss -
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.08,0:14:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,the great composers of the past, \Nall raised by Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.37,0:14:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I might stand alongside them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.33,0:14:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe in you, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.39,0:14:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Call me somehow odd, \Nbut I'm the one who's envious here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.57,0:14:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I can never be sure \Nwhich exact approach would work for you. {very unsure, lit: Luise, I don't know what specifications/way; method; means; resource; remedy you have}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.81,0:15:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as you like it, \Nyou should keep playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the piano will become your friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.81,0:15:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.15,0:15:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... See you around, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Berlin performance cancelled?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.42,0:15:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sudden illness? \NOr did someone get in an accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.90,0:15:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd be petty, compared to reality. {no clue, lit: if that had been the case, we would have also resigned/gave up - maybe he means "we should dig this further"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.89,0:15:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Palfy and Maria Therese seem to have had a beef. {clash; skirmish; conflict; discord; quarrel; brush}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Indignant, she threw a tantrum and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.50,0:15:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, which means, Palfy is to bear the blame?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.16,0:15:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Palfy is playing an important part of a conductor, \Nso getting along with Maria Therese is among his duties. {he had a responsibility to get along with ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.58,0:15:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn't this duty mutual, for Maria Therese as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.82,0:15:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Her snobbishness makes up half of her fame by now. {/her selfishness if famous}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to be a fan of Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.00,0:15:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Quite the opposite! \NI find him rather sickening.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.56,0:15:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will always keep saying that conflicts \Nshould be judged from a position of impartiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.75,0:16:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Maria Therese, someone has to teach you some tact!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.54,0:16:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be so snot-nosed? {/too selfish}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.84,0:16:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To be taken seriously as an artist, \Nyou learn some modesty first! {unsure: as an artist, to do taisei/taisen, ... - taisei/sen can be a fuckton of things that I won't even bother listing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.15,0:16:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at the very least, I get to return home so soon. \NCan you even imagine Luise's rapture when she finds out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.88,0:16:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot tell for certain, \Nwhich approach would work for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.48,0:16:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But as long as you like it, \Nyou should keep playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.79,0:17:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Herr Palfy! \NYoung Fraulein is also here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.43,0:17:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's highly convenient. {/just what I needed}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.10,0:17:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Need a hand with this luggage?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.80,0:17:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? No, no, I'm good.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.69,0:17:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.42,0:17:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.88,0:17:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Luise bring along some friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.10,0:18:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.66,0:18:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.97,0:18:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, very soothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.50,0:18:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The warmth channeled straight into your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.86,0:18:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Bravo! Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.64,0:18:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You were practicing in secret, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just that, even without my teaching, \Nyou managed to become that good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.46,0:18:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"When a child is a genius..." No,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.06,0:18:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,"Exactly {\i1}because{\i0} the child is this way!" {no clue, just absolute 0, "child is a genius, no, should I say it's the child exactly" - maybe "my daughter is a genius like me"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.07,0:19:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The change that the summer camp \Ncaused in Luise is miraculous! {/changed since ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.06,0:19:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It emancipates the mind, makes a new, better self out of you, \Nboth as an artist and as a human! {lit: throwing away the fuki/fuuki and looking for the new - no clue, fuki may be a shitton of things; lit: both art and humanity - no clue what's humanity to do here, I hate this sentence overall}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.46,0:19:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you don't mind me \Nplaying piano from now on, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.08,0:19:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for the life of it. {/isn;t it obvious}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.88,0:19:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you're daddy's dear girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.97,0:19:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.81,0:19:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,"I am daddy's dear girl."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.63,0:19:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This little thought, seemingly so obvious \Nhad only now been grasped by Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.63,0:19:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The delight of just being able to keep playing the piano, \Nwas soon to be displaced by an even greater joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.26,0:19:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But for now, in her little heart, Lotte is merely praying \Nfor this moment of happiness to last forever.
Comment: 0,0:20:20.17,0:20:20.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.11,0:20:29.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.64,0:20:33.10,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.10,0:20:36.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.82,0:20:39.73,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.95,0:20:51.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.37,0:20:55.13,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.13,0:20:58.67,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.67,0:21:02.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.51,0:21:05.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.09,0:21:08.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:13.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.19,0:21:17.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.89,0:21:22.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.54,0:21:25.95,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:29.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.58,0:21:32.35,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.40,0:21:37.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.17,0:21:40.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.17,0:21:44.17,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:45.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode preview
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:50.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,We switched places!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.55,0:21:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I had this thought haunting me lately. \NWhy did our dad and mom break up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.72,0:21:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? I've also been thinking the exact same thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.16,0:22:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Then, there's a quick solution. {lit: the story is fast/short - no clue}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.63,0:22:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason for dad and mom's break-up - \Nwe'll find it out ourselves! We'll become detectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean we'll interrogate them two?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.24,0:22:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly. We'll get the answer out of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.36,0:22:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself: \N Little Detective Agency.{小さな探偵団} Don't miss it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.00,0:22:13.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 11\N Little Detective Agency {小さな探偵団}
